# Full automation playbook

**Primary path for a new app + deploy:** read and follow the Cursor skill **`create-app-and-deploy`** (`.cursor/skills/create-app-and-deploy/SKILL.md`) — topic-specific code + `.\scripts\nanoclaw-deploy.ps1 -AppName <slug>`.

When the user says "create the app", "deploy end-to-end", "full deploy", "create an app and deploy it", or names a **new** product (not just redeploy), use that skill. Legacy step-by-step below still applies if you need granular GitHub/Vercel/Neon/Render commands without nanoclaw.

## 1. Ensure GitHub repo exists
- Run: `.\scripts\github-create-repo.ps1 -Name <AppName>` (or the repo name for this project)
- If the repo already exists, script exits cleanly. Then ensure remote: `git remote add origin git@github.com:rohinisd/Habit.git` only if `git remote -v` shows no origin. Then: `git add .`, `git commit -m "..."` if there are changes, `git branch -M main`, `git push -u origin main`.

## 2. Ensure Vercel project exists (frontend)
- **One-time:** If Vercel is not yet linked to the GitHub repo, run `.\scripts\vercel-install-github.ps1` to open the install page; the user must click Install and select the repo (this cannot be automated via API with a user token).
- Run: `.\scripts\vercel-create-project.ps1 -ProjectName habit -RepoOwner rohinisd -RepoName Habit`
- Then deploy: `.\scripts\deploy.ps1` (or `npx vercel deploy --prod --token=$env:VERCEL_TOKEN --yes`). If the project has no frontend yet (no app/ or package.json with Next.js), skip Vercel deploy until the frontend exists.

## 3. Neon (database)
- **Ensure Neon project exists:** run `.\scripts\neon-create-project.ps1 -Name habit -UpdateEnv`. This creates a project via API and writes `DATABASE_URL` and `NEON_PROJECT_ID` to `.env`. If the account already has a project, use that: run `.\scripts\neon-connection-string.ps1 -UpdateEnv -Pooled` instead to refresh `DATABASE_URL`.
- Then run migrations if any: `.\scripts\neon-run-sql.ps1 scripts\migrations\001_init.sql` (create the SQL file if the app needs tables).

## 4. Render (backend, if app has a backend)
- If the app has a backend (e.g. FastAPI in `backend/`): either use existing `RENDER_SERVICE_ID` (deploys that service) or create a new service: `.\scripts\render-create-service.ps1 -Name habit-api -RepoUrl https://github.com/rohinisd/Habit -Branch main -RootDir backend -DockerfilePath backend/Dockerfile`. Add the returned service ID to `.env` as `RENDER_SERVICE_ID`, then run `.\scripts\render-deploy.ps1`.

## 5. Summary
- Run commands in sequence. Do not ask "shall I run this?". If a step fails (e.g. repo exists, project exists), continue. After automation, report: repo URL, Vercel URL (if deployed), Render URL (if backend), Neon connected (if DB).
